        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 27 at 8:53AM CDT by NWS Corpus Christi TX</headline>
        <description>At 852 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from near Chaparral Wildlife Management Area to 6
miles southwest of Light to near Gilson Groves to Chupadera Ranch
Airport. Movement was southeast at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Cotulla, Artesia Wells, Chupadera Ranch Airport, and Chaparral
Wildlife Management Area.

This includes the following highways...
Interstate 35 between mile markers 47 and 70.
US Highway 83 between mile markers 668 and 672.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
